{%- comment -%}
  templates/index.liquid — Crema Italia storefront (POC3)

  A single-document SPA: every "page" below is a .page block, toggled client-side
  by showPage() in ci-storefront.js. Editorial copy is authored here in Liquid; the
  catalog grids, roaster profiles, product detail, cart and account views are filled
  at runtime from assets/ci-catalog.json (the baked-in test dataset).

  This renders only once Shopify password protection is OFF, or to a password-holder
  previewing the theme. While pre-launch, visitors still see templates/password.liquid.

  Production note: when the live store is built, the JS-rendered grids are replaced by
  real Liquid loops over {{ collection.products }} + crema_italia.* metafields, and the
  Roccia subscription UI binds to native selling_plan_groups (Loop). Integration points
  are flagged with <!-- LOOP --> / <!-- PROD --> comments.
{%- endcomment -%}

<!-- ============================== HOME ============================== -->
<div class="page active" id="page-home">
  <div class="hero"><div class="hero-inner">
    <img class="hero-logo" src="{{ 'ci-logo-knockout.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Crema Italia">
    <h1>Meet our curated group of Italian Roasters and their roasts.</h1>
    <p class="subhead">Italian Artisan Coffee, Imported Without Compromise.</p>
    <div class="tricolore" aria-hidden="true"><div></div><div></div><div></div></div>
    <div class="hero-btns">
      <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="showPage('sorpresa')">Begin with a Sorpresa Tour</button>
      <button class="btn btn-outline" onclick="showPage('roccia')">Build a Roccia Subscription</button>
    </div>
  </div></div>
  <main class="ci-main">
    <div class="section-head" style="margin-top:0"><p class="eyebrow">How the catalog is organized</p><h2>The four coffee shelves.</h2></div>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <div class="shelf-card" onclick="showPage('roccia')"><h3>Roccia</h3><div class="ss2">The Rock · Subscription (and one-time ordering)</div><p>Your preferred coffee, size, and cadence — free shipping and a 10% discount.</p></div>
      <div class="shelf-card" onclick="showPage('sorpresa')"><h3>Sorpresa</h3><div class="ss2">Discovery · One-time</div><p>Our curated collection of roasted delights. On-demand 100g Tour bundles — the best way to find your favorite roast subscription.</p></div>
      <div class="shelf-card" onclick="showPage('selezione')"><h3>Selezione</h3><div class="ss2">Premium &amp; Seasonal · One-time</div><p>Roasters' premium and seasonal offerings. Micro-lots and limited imports. When a product sells out, it may not return — once it's gone, it's gone.</p></div>
      <div class="shelf-card" onclick="showPage('offerta')"><h3>Offerta</h3><div class="ss2">The Opportunity · One-time</div><p>Limited-time offers, on sale while inventory lasts. Good coffee approaching its freshness window, priced honestly. Sold as-is.</p></div>
    </div>

    <div class="tour-hero">
      <div class="tour-hero-text">
        <p class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--ci-crema-light)">Featured Tour · Sorpresa</p>
        <h2>Tour d'Italia 1</h2>
        <p>Three different 100g bags from three roasters, our choice — assembled on-demand so every bag ships fresh. A printed tasting card names each roaster and their notes.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:.5rem;color:var(--ci-crema-light);font-style:italic">$77.70 · assembled to order</p>
        <button class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top:1rem" onclick="openProduct('tour-ditalia-1')">See the Tour</button>
      </div>
      <div class="tour-bags"><div class="tour-bag">Gardelli<br>Ethiopia</div><div class="tour-bag">La Sosta<br>Guatemala</div><div class="tour-bag">Fusari<br>Colombia</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Our roasters</p><h2>A small group, each with a big story.</h2></div>
    <div class="card-grid" id="home-roasters"></div>

    <div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Our model</p><h2>Curated, never aggregated.</h2></div>
    <div class="prose" style="max-width:72ch">
      <p>We do not roast, grind, blend, or alter the roasters' packaging. Instead, we carefully choose a small number of roasters whose work represents the craft of Italian roasting at its finest, and we present their coffee exactly as they produced and sealed it — whole bean, in valve bags, fresh and ready to consume.</p>
      <p>Your first purchase is our introduction. You may already know the roaster by reputation and are ready to subscribe, but if not, try Sorpresa — we'll introduce you to a roaster you'll fall in love with, and hope that a Roccia subscription will soon follow.</p>
      <p>We are the U.S. Agent for FDA food-facility registration on behalf of our roaster partners. We import and airfreight a limited supply of pallets, matching the cadence of our customers and roasters to maximize the fresh-roasted flavor you deserve.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">The Crema Italia Promise</p><h2>Three things we mean.</h2></div>
    <ul class="promise-list">
      <li><div class="pn">1</div><div class="pt"><h3>Curated with love, never aggregated.</h3><p>A small group of Italian roasters — carefully chosen, not collected.</p></div></li>
      <li><div class="pn">2</div><div class="pt"><h3>Love your first bag, or we send a different one — free.</h3><p>On Roccia, Sorpresa, and Selezione. Offerta is sold as-is (see <button class="inline-link" onclick="showPage('promise')">the Promise page</button>).</p></div></li>
      <li><div class="pn">3</div><div class="pt"><h3>Cancel your subscription anytime in a couple of clicks.</h3><p>Pause, skip, swap, or cancel — all self-service, no minimum, no cancel fee.</p></div></li>
    </ul>

    <div class="callout" style="margin-top:2.5rem"><strong>Not sure where to start?</strong> Take the three-question taste quiz — we will filter the catalog to your preferences. <button onclick="openQuiz()" style="background:none;border:none;cursor:pointer;color:var(--ci-crema);font-weight:600;text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:2px;font-family:var(--ci-font-body)">Take the quiz</button></div>
  </main>
</div>

<!-- ============================== SHOP ============================== -->
<div class="page" id="page-shop">
  <main class="ci-main">
    <div class="section-head" style="margin-top:0"><p class="eyebrow">The catalog</p><h2>Shop</h2></div>
    <p class="pf-hint" id="pf-hint" style="display:none;margin-bottom:1rem">Filtered to your taste profile. <span onclick="clearProfile()">Clear profile</span></p>
    <div class="filter-bar">
      <div class="filter-row">
        <div class="filter-group"><div class="filter-label">Region</div><div class="filter-pills">
          <span class="pill active" onclick="filterRegion(this,'all')">All Regions</span>
          <span class="pill" onclick="filterRegion(this,'toscana')">Toscana</span>
          <span class="pill" onclick="filterRegion(this,'emilia')">Emilia-Romagna</span>
          <span class="pill disabled">Piemonte</span>
          <span class="pill disabled">Sicilia</span>
        </div></div>
        <div class="filter-group"><div class="filter-label">Shelf</div><div class="filter-pills">
          <span class="pill active" onclick="filterShelf(this,'all')">All</span>
          <span class="pill" onclick="filterShelf(this,'roccia')">Roccia</span>
          <span class="pill" onclick="filterShelf(this,'sorpresa')">Sorpresa</span>
          <span class="pill" onclick="filterShelf(this,'selezione')">Selezione</span>
          <span class="pill" onclick="filterShelf(this,'offerta')">Offerta</span>
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="filter-divider"></div>
      <div class="filter-row">
        <div class="filter-group"><div class="filter-label">Roast</div><div class="filter-pills">
          <span class="pill active" onclick="filterTaste(this,'roast','all')">Any</span>
          <span class="pill" onclick="filterTaste(this,'roast','light')">Light</span>
          <span class="pill" onclick="filterTaste(this,'roast','medium')">Medium</span>
          <span class="pill" onclick="filterTaste(this,'roast','dark')">Dark</span>
        </div></div>
        <div class="filter-group"><div class="filter-label">Flavor</div><div class="filter-pills">
          <span class="pill active" onclick="filterTaste(this,'flavor','all')">Any</span>
          <span class="pill" onclick="filterTaste(this,'flavor','fruit')">Fruit &amp; Floral</span>
          <span class="pill" onclick="filterTaste(this,'flavor','sweet')">Sweet &amp; Chocolate</span>
          <span class="pill" onclick="filterTaste(this,'flavor','terroir')">Bold &amp; Spiced</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flavor-desc" id="flavor-desc"></div></div>
        <div class="filter-group"><div class="filter-label">Caffeine</div><div class="filter-pills">
          <span class="pill active" onclick="filterTaste(this,'caffeine','all')">Any</span>
          <span class="pill" onclick="filterTaste(this,'caffeine','full')">Caffeinated</span>
          <span class="pill" onclick="filterTaste(this,'caffeine','decaf')">Decaf</span>
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="save-profile" id="save-profile"><button class="inline-link" onclick="saveToProfile()">Save these preferences to my taste profile</button></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid" id="shop-grid"></div>
    <div id="no-results" style="display:none;text-align:center;padding:3rem 1rem;color:var(--ci-mute)">
      <p style="font-weight:600;color:var(--ci-espresso)">No coffees match these filters right now.</p>
      <p style="font-size:.9rem;margin-top:.25rem">Try widening your taste profile, or <button onclick="clearProfile()" style="background:none;border:none;color:var(--ci-crema);font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;text-decoration:underline">clear filters</button>.</p>
    </div>
  </main>
</div>

<!-- ============================== ROCCIA ============================== -->
<div class="page" id="page-roccia">
  <div class="dark-hero"><div class="dark-hero-inner">
    <button class="back-btn" style="color:var(--ci-crema-light)" onclick="showPage('shop')">Back to shop</button>
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--ci-crema-light)">The Rock · Subscription (and one-time ordering)</p>
    <h1>Roccia</h1>
    <p class="sub">Our rock-solid subscription plan.</p>
    <p>Choose any roast from any roaster and receive it on your cadence — every 4, 6, or 8 weeks. Bag sizes 250g, 500g, and 1kg. Subscribers receive a 10% discount on all coffee subscriptions plus free U.S. shipping.</p>
    <div class="cn"><strong>Self-service, always.</strong> Pause anytime, skip anytime, swap roaster or bag up to 48 hours before the order locks, cancel anytime. No minimum commitment. No cancel fee.</div>
  </div></div>
  <main class="ci-main">
    <div class="callout">In addition, active Roccia subscribers unlock 10% savings on all Roccia, Sorpresa, and Selezione roasts, even one-off purchases. <em>Offerta and Bottega items are priced as-is and the Roccia discount does not apply.</em></div>
    <div class="founding-banner"><strong>Founding Members</strong> — the first 222 subscribers receive 12% instead of 10%. Only 172 of 222 founding slots remain.</div>
    <div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Available now · Toscana</p><h2>Roccia coffees</h2></div>
    <div class="card-grid" id="grid-roccia"></div>
    <div class="afd">We order freshly roasted beans by the pallet and they typically arrive every six weeks or so. In the event that we are short on a subscribed item, we'll provide you advanced notice with an option for you to wait for resupply, or to allow us to temporarily substitute a similar product from the same shelf, and never with an additional charge.</div>
  </main>
</div>

<!-- ============================== SORPRESA ============================== -->
<div class="page" id="page-sorpresa">
  <div class="dark-hero"><div class="dark-hero-inner">
    <button class="back-btn" style="color:var(--ci-crema-light)" onclick="showPage('shop')">Back to shop</button>
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--ci-crema-light)">Discovery · One-time</p>
    <h1>Sorpresa</h1>
    <p class="sub">Our curated collection of roasted delights.</p>
    <p>Named Tour bundles, our choice — three different 100g bags from three different roasters, assembled on-demand so every bag is fresh at shipment. Every Tour includes a printed tasting card naming each roaster and their notes. The aim of a Tour is simple: to lead you to the roaster you will want on a Roccia subscription.</p>
  </div></div>
  <main class="ci-main">
    <div class="tour-hero">
      <div class="tour-hero-text">
        <p class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--ci-crema-light)">Published now</p>
        <h2>Tour d'Italia 1</h2>
        <p>A journey across regions: North, Central, South. Three 100g bags — Gardelli Ethiopia, La Sosta Guatemala, Fusari Colombia — boxed with a tasting card.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:.5rem;color:var(--ci-crema-light);font-style:italic">$77.70 · assembled to order</p>
        <button class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top:1rem" onclick="openProduct('tour-ditalia-1')">View Tour</button>
      </div>
      <div class="tour-bags"><div class="tour-bag">Gardelli<br>Ethiopia</div><div class="tour-bag">La Sosta<br>Guatemala</div><div class="tour-bag">Fusari<br>Colombia</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="callout"><strong>Freshness-gated availability.</strong> A Tour is offered only while all three components are in stock and within their freshness window. If any component runs low or ages out, the Tour is paused — "This tour is temporarily unavailable. Check back soon." — and returns automatically when stock refreshes. If a component must be swapped after you order, we pair you with a comparable coffee from the same roaster and tell you in your confirmation.</div>
    <div class="afd">Our choice, never the roaster's choice — because we are the curator. Components are 100g only; Tours are never mixed-size.</div>
  </main>
</div>

<!-- ============================== SELEZIONE ============================== -->
<div class="page" id="page-selezione">
  <div class="dark-hero"><div class="dark-hero-inner">
    <button class="back-btn" style="color:var(--ci-crema-light)" onclick="showPage('shop')">Back to shop</button>
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--ci-crema-light)">Premium &amp; Seasonal · One-time</p>
    <h1>Selezione</h1>
    <p class="sub">Roasters' premium and seasonal offerings.</p>
    <p>Micro-lots, single-origin specialty bags, and limited-allocation imports. One-time purchase only — never a subscription. Supply is pallet-bound: when a Selezione SKU runs out, it may or may not return depending on the next pallet. We show honest scarcity only — a low-inventory note below twelve units, and a hard cap that prevents overselling. No countdown timers.</p>
    <div class="cn"><strong>Subscriber early access.</strong> Active Roccia subscribers see new Selezione SKUs 48 hours before the public listing.</div>
  </div></div>
  <main class="ci-main">
    <div class="card-grid" id="grid-selezione"></div>
  </main>
</div>

<!-- ============================== OFFERTA ============================== -->
<div class="page" id="page-offerta">
  <div class="dark-hero"><div class="dark-hero-inner">
    <button class="back-btn" style="color:var(--ci-crema-light)" onclick="showPage('shop')">Back to shop</button>
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--ci-crema-light)">The Opportunity · One-time</p>
    <h1>Offerta</h1>
    <p class="sub">Limited-time offers, on sale while inventory lasts.</p>
    <p>Coffee lots that have reached their Offerta threshold — still good, still within a real freshness window, priced down honestly. We show the original price struck through, the Offerta price beside it, and the actual remaining freshness window in plain words. No fake urgency, no countdown timers.</p>
    <div class="cn"><strong>Sold as-is.</strong> Offerta purchases carry a modified guarantee — material defects only. Freshness window is disclosed at purchase; no exchanges for age-related palate preferences. Coffee that falls outside its freshness window is removed from sale entirely and donated to Feeding Tampa Bay.</div>
  </div></div>
  <main class="ci-main">
    <div class="callout">At launch, Offerta is typically empty — coffee only arrives here as a lot ages past its threshold. The example below shows how an Offerta listing reads.</div>
    <div class="card-grid" id="grid-offerta"></div>
    <div class="afd">Offerta prices are set by markup tier, not by a percentage-off blast. Offerta items never appear on a roaster's own profile page — we protect each roaster's storefront.</div>
  </main>
</div>

